HEADWORD: Supraglotic
<hw>Su`pra*glot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated above the glottis; -- applied to that part of the cavity
of the larynx above the true vocal cords.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suprahepatic</ent>⟦br⟧
